<section class="about" id="about">
<div class="container">
<h2>About Ikat</h2>
<p>
Ikat weaving began as a home-based craft and gradually developed into a structured weaving tradition.
The weaving community mainly belongs to the Padmashali caste, known for skilled handloom weaving.
Ikat textiles are famous for lightweight fabric, geometric patterns, and vibrant colours.
Women also play a major role in yarn preparation, dyeing, and weaving.
</p>
</div>
